      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Smart Set</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Your writer described the picture of the students in the Science Seminar club, in his 1960's high-school yearbook, as betraying a ''tense, tight-lipped posture of defensiveness.'' Why then did you choose a similar type of picture for your cover?</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Your writer described the picture of the students in the Science Seminar club, in his 1960's high-school yearbook, as betraying a ''tense, tight-lipped posture of defensiveness.'' Why then did you choose a similar type of picture for your cover?</p>
        <p>In the 1950's, my husband and I were math-and-science kids at Abraham Lincoln High School in Brooklyn. He was captain of the city champion math team. What I recall most about the superbright kids of my day is their sense of humor and the fun we had.</p>
        <p>Sheila Bierman Blume, M.D.</p>
        <p>Sayville, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
